      "author": "levid",
      "description": "## HangarX v1.0.31\n\n### Async vault sync\nLarge vault imports no longer time out at Cloud Run's request cap. The plugin now opts every ingest call into the server's new **async mode**: the server returns 202 + a `syncJobId` immediately and runs harmonization in the background. The plugin tracks progress via the existing `/jobs/:id` polling endpoint. Vaults that previously 504-killed at ~15 minutes now complete cleanly regardless of size.\n\n### Credit-exhausted upgrade prompt\nWhen you hit your plan's credit limit mid-sync, the modal now shows a clear \"Credits exhausted\" banner with an **Open billing settings** link straight to your account. The sync stops cleanly instead of bombing through the rest of the queue with 429s — and the Notice surfaces the server's actual `upgradeMessage` so you know exactly what to upgrade to.\n\n### Typed errors (developer-facing)\n`CortexClient.req()` now throws a typed `CortexError` carrying HTTP status, error code, body, and the structured `upgradeUrl` / `upgradeMessage` / `creditsRemaining` from the server response. Method `isCreditsExhausted()` lets callers branch on 429s without parsing error strings.\n\n### Other\n- Internal: reranker provider config (Cohere / Jina) removed — those rerankers were no longer wired into the active extraction pipeline.\n\n### Compatibility\n- Min Obsidian: 1.5.0\n- Requires cortex-api v1.0.3+\n\nSee repo CHANGELOG for full history.",
